#X text 34 58 The [decay~] is the one object solely dedicated to decay only envelopes \, but we've seen other objects that are also useful and are also the main objects for envelope generation in Pd. Nonetheless \, we can still use mode objects. The [lag~] object was shown as something we can use just for setting a decay envelope and there are other similar objects that were previously introduced that can also be used \, like [autofade2~] \, [glide2~] \, [smooth2~] and even [slew2~]. All of these follow the same idea of setting the upward ramp to 0!, f 75;
#X text 232 295 A sine decay ramp, f 7;
#X obj 399 263 float2imp~;
#X obj 399 231 bng 21 250 50 0 empty empty empty 17 7 0 10 #dcdcdc #000000 #000000;
#X obj 335 327 out~;
#X obj 399 295 glide2~ -exp 4 0 1000;
#X obj 335 267 brown~;
#X obj 335 296 *~;
#X text 488 253 A quartic decay ramp, f 10;
#N canvas 561 177 567 451 slew 0;
